import React from 'react'
import { BrowserRouter, Route, Switch } from 'react-router-dom'


const NewsNavBar = () =>    {

    return (
        <BrowserRouter>
            <Switch>
                <React.Fragment>
                    <Route to='/news' className='news_navLink'>All</Route>
                    <Route to='/football' className='news_navLink'>Football</Route>
                    <Route to='/tennis' className='news_navLink'>Tennis</Route>
                    <Route to='/cricket' className='news_navLink'>Cricket</Route>
                    <Route to='/motorsport' className='news_navLink'>Motorsport</Route>
                    <Route to='/horse-racing' className='news_navLink'>Horse Racing</Route>
                    <Route to='/golf' className='news_navLink'>Golf</Route>
                    <Route to='/boxing' className='news_navLink'>Boxing</Route>
                    <Route to='/olympics' className='news_navLink'>Olympics</Route>
                    <Route to='/basketball' className='news_navLink'>Basketball</Route>         
                </React.Fragment>
            </Switch>
        </BrowserRouter>
       
    )
}

export default NewsNavBar
